# `::dropdown(select)` — Customizable Select Dropdown Pseudo-Element

I'm familiar with this relatively new CSS feature. The `::dropdown(select)` pseudo-element targets the dropdown popover part of a customizable `<select>` element, which is part of the new **customizable select** feature (previously known as "open UI select" or "styleable select").

This feature is opt-in: you enable it by setting `appearance: base-select` on the `<select>` element.

Here's a complete working example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>::dropdown(select) Demo</title>
<style>
  /* Opt in to the new customizable select */
  select {
    appearance: base-select;
    font-size: 1rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 2px solid #333;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background-color: #fff;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  /* Style the dropdown popover that contains the options */
  select::dropdown(select) {
    background-color: #1a1a2e;
    border: 2px solid #e94560;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  /* Style the individual options */
  select option {
    color: #eee;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: background-color 0.2s;
  }

  select option:hover {
    background-color: #e94560;
    color: #fff;
  }

  select option:checked {
    background-color: #0f3460;
    color: #fff;
  }

  /* Style the button part (the trigger) */
  select::select-arrow {
    /* The arrow indicator */
    display: block;
    content: "▼";
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #e94560;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Customizable <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> with <code>::dropdown(select)</code></h1>

  <label for="flavor">Choose a flavor:</label>
  <select id="flavor" name="flavor">
    <option value="">--Select a flavor--</option>
    <option value="vanilla">🍦 Vanilla</option>
    <option value="chocolate">🍫 Chocolate</option>
    <option value="strawberry">🍓 Strawberry</option>
    <option value="mint">🌿 Mint Chip</option>
    <option value="mango">🥭 Mango Sorbet</option>
  </select>
</body>
</html>
```

## Key Points

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **`appearance: base-select`** | Required on the `<select>` to opt into the customizable select UI. Without this, the pseudo-elements won't apply. |
| **`::dropdown(select)`** | Targets the popover/dropdown container that holds the `<option>` elements when the select is opened. |
| **`::select-arrow`** | Targets the arrow indicator inside the select button. |
| **Popover behavior** | The dropdown uses the **Popover API** under the hood, meaning it renders in the **top layer** and isn't clipped by `overflow: hidden` on ancestor elements. |
| **`::check(select)`** | Targets the checkmark indicator on the currently selected option. |

