| HTML Attributes | Description |
|---|---|
| `popover` or `popover="auto"` | Makes element a popover with light-dismiss behavior |
| `popover="manual"` | Makes element a popover without light-dismiss |
| `popovertarget="id"` | On a `<button>`, specifies which popover to control |
| `popovertargetaction="show\|hide\|toggle"` | Which action the button performs (default: `toggle`) |

| JavaScript Methods / Properties | Description |
|---|---|
| `element.showPopover()` | Shows the popover |
| `element.hidePopover()` | Hides the popover |
| `element.togglePopover(force?)` | Toggles the popover; optional boolean to force state |
| `element.popover` | Gets/sets the popover state (`"auto"`, `"manual"`, or `null`) |

| Events | Description |
|---|---|
| `toggle` | Fires after the popover's state changes (`event.newState` / `event.oldState`) |
