Here's what actually shipped and what I *do* know:

## The View Transitions API (what `@page-transition` evolved into)

The early drafts used `@page-transition` but the final API uses:

- **JavaScript:** `document.startViewTransition(callback)`
- **CSS pseudo-elements:** `::view-transition`, `::view-transition-group(name)`, `::view-transition-image-pair(name)`, `::view-transition-old(name)`, `::view-transition-new(name)`
- **CSS property:** `view-transition-name`

Here's working code using the **real, shipped View Transitions API**:

### HTML
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>View Transitions Demo</title>
  <style>
    /* Assign view-transition-name to elements you want to animate */
    .box {
      view-transition-name: box-transition;
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      background: coral;
      border-radius: 8px;
      display: grid;
      place-content: center;
      font-family: sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: white;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: none;
    }

    .box.expanded {
      width: 300px;
      height: 300px;
      background: teal;
      border-radius: 50%;
    }

    /* Customize the view transition animation */
    ::view-transition-old(box-transition) {
      animation: fade-out 0.3s ease-in forwards;
    }

    ::view-transition-new(box-transition) {
      animation: fade-in 0.3s ease-out forwards;
    }

    /* Default root transition (crossfade of the whole page snapshot) */
    ::view-transition-old(root) {
      animation-duration: 0.3s;
    }

    ::view-transition-new(root) {
      animation-duration: 0.3s;
    }

    @keyframes fade-out {
      from { opacity: 1; }
      to   { opacity: 0; }
    }

    @keyframes fade-in {
      from { opacity: 0; }
      to   { opacity: 1; }
    }

    body {
      display: grid;
      place-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      margin: 0;
      background: #1a1a2e;
    }
