### Cross-Document View Transitions (MPA - Multi-Page Apps)

For cross-document (MPA) view transitions, the newer spec uses a CSS `@view-transition` at-rule (not `@page-transition`):

```css
/* Enable cross-document view transitions (in both pages) */
@view-transition {
  navigation: auto;
}

/* On the old page */
.hero-image {
  view-transition-name: hero;
}

/* On the new page */
.hero-image {
  view-transition-name: hero;
}

/* Customize the animation */
::view-transition-group(hero) {
  animation-duration: 0.4s;
  animation-timing-function: ease-in-out;
}
```

