## Key Points

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| `@view-transition { navigation: auto; }` | Opts the page into cross-document view transitions for **same-origin** navigations |
| `view-transition-name` | Assigns a unique name to an element so it can be matched across pages and animated independently (instead of the default whole-page crossfade) |
| `::view-transition-old(name)` | Pseudo-element representing the **old** (outgoing) snapshot |
| `::view-transition-new(name)` | Pseudo-element representing the **new** (incoming) snapshot |
| `::view-transition-group(name)` | Pseudo-element that wraps both old and new, useful for animating size/position changes |

## Customizing with JavaScript (Optional)

You can use the `pageswap` and `pagereveal` events to customize transitions per-navigation:

