# Cross-Document View Transitions using @view-transition

Here's the CSS/HTML code to enable cross-document (multi-page) view transitions:

## CSS (add to both pages)

```css
/* Opt in to cross-document view transitions */
@view-transition {
  navigation: auto;
}

/* Optional: Define custom animations for page transitions */
@keyframes move-out {
  from {
    transform: translateY(0%);
  }
  to {
    transform: translateY(-100%);
  }
}

@keyframes move-in {
  from {
    transform: translateY(100%);
  }
  to {
    transform: translateY(0%);
  }
}

/* Apply animations to outbound and inbound page states */
::view-transition-old(root) {
  animation: 0.4s ease-in both move-out;
}

::view-transition-new(root) {
  animation: 0.4s ease-in both move-in;
}
```

## With View Transition Types

```css
/* Opt in with custom types */
@view-transition {
  navigation: auto;
  types: slide;
}

/* Or multiple types */
@view-transition {
  navigation: auto;
  types: slide fade-in;
}
```

