Here's the actual working code using the CSS Scroll-driven Animations specification (shipped in Chrome 115+).

## Core Concepts

- `animation-timeline: scroll()` — ties animation progress to scroll position
- `animation-timeline: view()` — ties animation progress to element's visibility in viewport
- `@keyframes` — define what animates
- `animation-range` — controls when in the scroll/view timeline the animation runs

