"""
Here is a concrete example using the CSS Anchor Positioning API. 

This code tethers a tooltip (the anchored element) to a button (the anchor element). The tooltip is positioned directly below the button, aligning its left edge with the button's left edge.

### HTML
```html
<button class="anchor-button">Hover me</button>
<div class="tooltip">I am anchored to the button!</div>
```

### CSS
```css
/* 1. Define the anchor element */
.anchor-button {
  /* Give the anchor a globally unique custom identifier */
  anchor-name: --my-tooltip-anchor;

  /* Basic styling */
  padding: 10px 20px;
  background-color: #007bff;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* 2. Define the anchored element */
.tooltip {
  /* The anchored element must be absolutely or fixed positioned */
  position: absolute;

  /* Link this element to the specific anchor identifier */
  position-anchor: --my-tooltip-anchor;

  /* 3. Use the anchor() function to position relative to the anchor's edges */
  /* Align the top edge of the tooltip to the bottom edge of the anchor */
  top: anchor(bottom);

  /* Align the left edge of the tooltip to the left edge of the anchor */
  left: anchor(left);

  /* Add a small gap between the anchor and the tooltip */
  margin-top: 8px;

  /* Basic styling */
  padding: 8px 12px;
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  border-radius: 4px;
  width: max-content;
}
```

