*   **`anchor-name`**: Applied to the button (`--my-tooltip-anchor`), making it an available anchor reference in the document.
*   **`position-anchor`**: Applied to the tooltip, telling it to use `--my-tooltip-anchor` as its default reference point for any `anchor()` functions.
*   **`anchor()`**: Used inside physical inset properties (`top`, `left`). Because `position-anchor` was declared, `anchor(bottom)` evaluates the bottom edge of `--my-tooltip-anchor`, and `anchor(left)` evaluates to the anchor's left edge.

